cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.DS 

The paper deals with multimedia phylogeny, which involves analyzing the evolutionary processes that influence digital objects and collections over time. This topic is closely related to multimedia analysis and computer vision (cs.MM, cs.CV), as well as information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes a two-tiered approach to searching for related images, which involves filtering a large pool of objects, a task that is often tackled using data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
